theorem Topology.interior_union_frontier_eq_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ∪ frontier (A : Set X) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  calc
    interior (A : Set X) ∪ frontier (A : Set X)
        = interior (A : Set X) ∪
          (closure (A : Set X) \ interior (A : Set X)) := rfl
    _ = interior (A : Set X) ∪ closure (A : Set X) := by
      simpa using
        Set.union_diff_self (s := interior (A : Set X))
          (t := closure (A : Set X))
    _ = closure (A : Set X) := by
      have h : (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
        intro x hx
        exact subset_closure hx
      simpa using (Set.union_eq_self_of_subset_left h)

theorem Topology.isClosed_P3_implies_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed A → Topology.P3 A → Topology.P1 A := by
  intro hClosed hP3
  intro x hxA
  -- From `P3`, obtain that `x ∈ interior (closure A)`.
  have hx_int_cl : x ∈ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := hP3 hxA
  -- Since `A` is closed, `closure A = A`, hence `x ∈ interior A`.
  have hx_int : x ∈ interior (A : Set X) := by
    simpa [hClosed.closure_eq] using hx_int_cl
  -- Any point of `interior A` lies in `closure (interior A)`.
  exact (subset_closure (s := interior A) hx_int)

theorem Topology.closure_eq_interior_closure_union_frontier
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) =
      interior (closure (A : Set X)) ∪ frontier (A : Set X) := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hxCl
    by_cases hIntCl : x ∈ interior (closure (A : Set X))
    · exact Or.inl hIntCl
    ·
      -- `x` is not in `interior (closure A)`; we show it lies in the frontier.
      have hNotIntA : x ∉ interior (A : Set X) := by
        intro hIntA
        have : x ∈ interior (closure (A : Set X)) :=
          (interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)) hIntA
        exact hIntCl this
      have hxFront : x ∈ frontier (A : Set X) :=
        And.intro hxCl hNotIntA
      exact Or.inr hxFront
  · intro h
    cases h with
    | inl hIntCl => exact interior_subset hIntCl
    | inr hFront => exact hFront.1
